     NAME
        fillbar.image-- Show the percentage of some work using a image.                 (V43)
 
     SUPERCLASS
        imageclass
 
     DESCRIPTION
        The fillbar.image image class provides a gauge that displays some
        ammount of work being done.
 
     METHODS
        OM_NEW--Create the FILLBAR image.  Passed to superclass, then OM_SET.
 
        OM_DISPOSE--Dispose the composite objects used by our class. Next
            control is passed to the superclass OM_DISPOSE method.
 
        OM_SET--Set object attributes.  Passed to superclass first.
 
        OM_UPDATE--Set object notification attributes.  Passed to superclass
            first.
 
        IM_DRAW--Renders the images.  Overrides the superclass.
 
        All other methods are passed to the superclass, including OM_DISPOSE.
 
     ATTRIBUTES
        SYSIA_DrawInfo (struct DrawInfo *) -- Contains important pen
            information.  This is required if IA_BGPen and IA_FGPen are
            not specified.
 
        IA_FGPen (LONG)    -- Pen to use to draw the Frame around the fillbar
            and all rendered text. If -1 is specified then TEXTPEN is used.
            Defaults to the -1 case.
 
        IA_BGPen (LONG)    -- Pen to use to draw the unlit segments or
            background.  If -1 is specified then BACKGROUNDPEN is used.
            Defaults to the -1 case.
        
        IA_FillPen  (LONG) -- Pen to use to draw the filled part of the
            fillbar. If -1 is specified then the FILLPEN is used.
            Defaults to the -1 case.
        
        IA_LeftEdge (LONG) -- Left edge to position image.

        IA_TopEdge  (LONG) -- Top edge to position image.
        
        IA_Width    (LONG) -- Width of the image.
 
        IA_Height   (LONG) -- Height of the image.
 
        FILLBAR_FillPen (LONG) -- Pen to use to fill the image. If -1 is
            specified then FILLPEN is used.
 
        FILLBAR_LabelLeft, FILLBAR_LabelRight (BOOL) -- if TRUE show the 0%
            and/or 100% labels in the fillbar. Defaults to TRUE.
        
        FILLBAR_LabelLeftString, FILLBAR_LabelRightString (STRPTR) -- choose
            the strings to the corresponding labels.
            Default to "  0%" and "100%".
        
        FILLBAR_LabelInside (BOOL) -- if TRUE show a floating % value in
            the middle of the fillbar. Defaults to TRUE.
            
        FILLBAR_FrameAround (BOOL) -- if TRUE the composite fillbar image
            object has a embossed frame around it. Defaults to TRUE.
            
        FILLBAR_FrameInside (BOOL) -- if TRUE the fillbar has a embossed frame
            around it. Defaults to TRUE.
        
        FILLBAR_Value (LONG) -- set the current value of the fillbar.
            Defaults to 0.
